Jerry, Howard, Emily, Robert, Troy, Rowland,  Eduardo, Dan, Calvin, Jacklyn=
, Mawuena, John, Enoh, Joe, Jing, Breck, and Zeyi, hello.

We are on track to launch the "Up our game Canada" program on Friday, Feb 2=
1.

The four modules being developed for the launch include:

  *
SME Strategies to Confront U.S. Tariff Threats (the new video produced by E=
noh is at: https://app.heygen.com/share/1ef2e8602db644e7a92ab0bf471e8cbc)
  *
Academic Insights for Canadian SME exporters
  *
Market diversification
  *
Short-term cost reduction

Each module includes a video, slide deck, a workbook, and presentation.

The "Up our game Canada" program is organized into five sections:

  1.
SME Strategies to Confront U.S. Tariff Threats
  2.
Sector Specific
  3.
Academic Insights for Canadian SME exporters
  4.
Policy, economic, geopolitical dimensions
  5.
Outlook

The section, "SME strategies to confront U.S. Tariff Threat," includes:

  *
Short-term cost reduction: strategies that can be implemented quickly to of=
fset immediate tariff impacts
  *
Market diversification: strategies that explore new opportunities to reduce=
 dependence on the U.S. market
  *
Long-term adjustments: strategies that require investment but offer sustain=
able solutions
  *
Collaboration and advocacy: strategies focused on collective action to infl=
uence trade policies
  *
Value added and differentiation: strategies that enhance product appeal and=
 retain customer loyalty despite higher prices

The new video "SME strategies to confront U.S. Tariff Threat," produced by =
Enoh is at: https://app.heygen.com/share/1ef2e8602db644e7a92ab0bf471e8cbc<h=
ttps://can01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fapp.heyg=
en.com%2Fshare%2F1ef2e8602db644e7a92ab0bf471e8cbc&data=3D05%7C02%7CBeiqiaoH=
