Our "Up our game Canada" corpus (41 articles, 2 slide decks, and 51 links) =
is housed in NotebookLM and Perplexity Space. You will be able to interact =
with our corpus and slide decks including asking whatever questions you wan=
t! More on this once we come up for a bit of air.

The first Perplexity workshop was a tremendous success. The workshop was de=
livered by Joe Hu in SP 102 on Monday Jan 20. Joe will deliver the second P=
erplexity workshop at TIM@Kanata on Monday, February 3.

If you have feedback on the new video, questions or need additional informa=
tion, please reach out.

Warm regards.

Tony B.

